verbose_text: NSP1 alters IFN-beta expression [XREF_BIBR]; 285 host cellular proteins have been identified that interact with NSP2 in PRRSV infected cells [XREF_BIBR]; NSP5 interacts with the host membrane, anchoring the viral RNA synthesizing machinery to modified intracellular membranes [XREF_BIBR], and it features T-cell epitopes [XREF_BIBR]; NSP7 features antigenic epitopes important in induction of host humoral immune response [XREF_BIBR]; NSP9 and NSP10 contain potential T-cell epitope [XREF_BIBR].
